The defendant Aaron J Janes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Aaron J Janes is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

records.addlTxt:
9:03 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty John Selsing.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement  - defendant will plea to Disorderly Conduct domestic and count 1 will be dismissed.  State concurs.  Atty Selsing concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 2 as charged and orders count 1 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Selsing.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

60 days county jail, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 1 year.

CONDITIONS:

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court grants 1 day of sentence credit if probation becomes revoked.

Court adjourned at 9:10 a.m.
Status hearing on April 18, 2016 at 09:00 am.
Sentencing hearing on April 18, 2016 at 09:00 am.
